A ranch dressing has a combination of creaminess from buttermilk, sour cream, sometimes mayonnaise, and herbs often parsley, thyme, and dill. Apart from salad it really goes well with a barbeque of chicken, pork, and choma. Ingredients Preparation Step 1 In a bowl whisk all ingredients together Step 2 Pour in enough mayo and sour cream to make the dressing the consistency you like. Step 3 Taste and adjust salt and pepper to your preference. Put in the refrigerator for an hour. Serve with your favorite salad or beef.